1. Operations Management

Oversee all hospital operations (clinical, nursing, administrative, billing, HR, IT, facilities).
Implement SOPs to ensure smooth functioning and compliance with NABH standards.
Monitor patient care quality, safety standards, and grievance redressal.
Lead regular performance review meetings with departmental heads.
2. Business Development & Marketing

Design and execute marketing strategies to increase patient inflow, brand visibility, and community engagement.
Build corporate tie-ups, TPA/insurance relationships, and referral networks with doctors.
Drive digital campaigns, outreach programs, CME events, and health camps.
Track ROI on marketing spends and optimize campaigns accordingly.
3. Strategic Leadership

Assist top management in long-term planning, expansion, and new service lines.
Ensure achievement of revenue, EBITDA, and patient satisfaction targets.
Introduce cost-control measures without compromising quality of care.
Represent the hospital/unit in public forums, associations, and partner events.
4. People & Performance

Mentor and manage departmental HODs and staff.
Build a performance-driven culture with clear KPIs/KRAs.
Ensure training & development programs are aligned to service excellence.
