Standardization and Documentation: Author, review, and approve all critical operational documentation, including Standard Operating Procedures (SOPs), rule books, and emergency response manuals, ensuring they align with the semi-high-speed environment and industry best practices.
Incident and Emergency Management: Design and implement comprehensive emergency plans and lead the immediate response and investigation of major incidents or severe service disruptions, focusing on minimizing downtime and passenger impact.
Operational Readiness and Training: Oversee the entire operational readiness program, including defining the competency framework, developing specialized training modules, and certifying all operational staff (e.g., train controllers, drivers, station personnel) prior to the launch of commercial service.
